  "chapter": {
    "number": 18,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Bildad: God Punishes the Wicked"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "Then Bildad the Shuhite replied:"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“How long until you end these speeches?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Show some sense, and then we can talk.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Why are we regarded as cattle,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "as stupid in your sight?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You who tear yourself in anger—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "should the earth be forsaken on your account,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "or the rocks be moved from their place?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Indeed, the lamp of the wicked is extinguished;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the flame of his fire does not glow.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The light in his tent grows dark,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the lamp beside him goes out.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "His vigorous stride is shortened,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and his own schemes trip him up.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For his own feet lead him into a net,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and he wanders into its mesh.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A trap seizes his heel;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "a snare grips him.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A noose is hidden in the ground,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and a trap lies in his path.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Terrors frighten him on every side",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and harass his every step.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "His strength is depleted,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and calamity is ready at his side.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "It devours patches of his skin;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the firstborn of death devours his limbs.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He is torn from the shelter of his tent",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and is marched off to the king of terrors.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Fire resides in his tent;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "burning sulfur rains down on his dwelling.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The roots beneath him dry up,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the branches above him wither away.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The memory of him perishes from the earth,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and he has no name in the land.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He is driven from light into darkness",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and is chased from the inhabited world.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He has no offspring or posterity among his people,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "no survivor where he once lived.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Those in the west are appalled at his fate,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "while those in the east tremble in horror.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Surely such is the dwelling of the wicked",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the place of one who does not know God.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": []
  },
